narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I gained an excellent introduction to German. I know how to speak basic German in a conversational setting.
I learned how to speak beginner level of German
This was a great course that taught the beginning level of the German language. Through this class I learned that speaking is a critical part of learning a language.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: You have online homework due twice a week. Those can be time-consuming, but if you start them early, you'll be fine. The tests are fair. If you put in effort in learning the content, you'll earn a good grade.
This course was amazing. The homework and communication with the school in Germany really helped reinforce concepts we were learning in class.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! If you're interesting in learning German, GMAN 110 is a great place to start.
Yes I would, anyone wanting to learn a new language should take this course, the workload is not too great and everyone in the German department is very nice
I would recommend this course to another student. The German language is extremely interesting and Professor Sippel was amazing to learn under.
